Morton Community Bank Cycling Classic
description: Peoria Bicycle Club after 23 years is moving the annual criterium to Morton, IL.  The Morton Commmunity Bank Cycling Classic is part of the 2011 Illinois Cup and features a $4000 payout and races for 13 categories.
course: The course is a 0.7 mile rectangle in downtown Morton, Il.  The start finish is at the intersection of Main and Adams and a clockwise course to Jefferson, 1st Ave, Wick St. and back to Main St.
registration: Registration will be day of, on-line at BikeReg.com or mail in to Peoria Bicycle Club, 704 Firethorn Dr., Washington, IL, 61571
directions: Start/Finish is at 200 S. Main, Morton, IL, 61550.  I-74 Exit 101 to I-155 South.  Drive 1 mile to Exit 31 Birchwood Ave.  Rt on Birchwood to Main St.  Left on Main St. to course.

title: Morton Community Bank Kid's Classic
description: Morton Community Bank Celebrity Bike Race and Kid\'s Bicycle race
course: Celebrity race will be on Main St. from Adams to Jefferson.  Kid\'s race will be on Adams between Main and Plum.
registration: Registration will be day of event by signing a USAC 2011 Standard Release
notes: Celebrity race will be by invitation and use supplied tricycles.  Kid\'s race will be on trikes and bicycles.
directions: I-74 Exit 102 South on Morton Ave.  Right at Jackson and left at Main St to course.
